title: Several changes to stunnel support to reduce complexity and improve security.
message:
Several changes to stunnel support to reduce complexity and improve security.

Now using validateX509Cert() for both X509Tunnel and SecureTunnel. That
function always saves the cert data upon user approval and then treats it as
definitive for future connections.

Moved the code responsible for setting up the secure tunnel to RfbProto to
be in line with how VeNCrypt and AnonTLS support is implemented.

No longer saving hashId and hashIdAlgorithm, as they are pertinent only for
the initial connection establishment.

Improved messages for related dialogs and translations to Russian are included.

title: Bugfix for Mac OS X when screen-sharing is done by password.
message:
Bugfix for Mac OS X when screen-sharing is done by password.

The addition of auth type 30 had broken backward compatibility with
Mac OS X machines configured to share screen if a client authenticates
via a VNC password. bVNC was picking auth type 30 even if the user name
field was not set in the settings, and when this auth type was chosen
Mac OS X was expecting a user name to be passed as well as the password
for that user name rather than a VNC password. Now, if a user name is not
supplied to bVNC, auth type 30 is not chosen and authentication falls
through to auth type 2.

title: How ignoring left Alt only if keyboard ID indicates that it is the default…
message:
How ignoring left Alt only if keyboard ID indicates that it is the default hardware keyboard (is 0).

This allows us to use it for symbol input on such keyboards and for Alt in any other scenario.

Additionally, a bugfix for aRDP and aSPICE where a static method needed to become public in aRDP.java
and aSPICE.java.

Finally, there is a bugfix for aSPICE where the native libraries were loaded in aSPICE and if an
intent is used to start RemoteCanvasActivity directly they would not be loaded. The loading of
native libs and initializing of Gstreamer was moved back to SpiceCommunicator.java.

- Implemented smooth scaling
- Implemented snap to 1:1 scaling to ease returning to 1:1.
- Implemented speed-based mouse scrolling with two-finger swipe.
- Fixed the calculation of the minimum scale to allow up to and including fit-to-screen scaling in Zoomable scaling mode.
- Various bug-fixes.

title: - improvements to intro text  layout for small screens
message:
- improvements to intro text  layout for small screens
- corrected minimum SDK version due to use of pointer indexes (min api 8).

title: new layout for large screens, tweaked layout for normal screens, modified…
message: new layout for large screens, tweaked layout for normal screens, modified minimum SDK version required to 4.

title: added some very short sleeps between down and up events to accommodate windows…
message: added some very short sleeps between down and up events to accommodate windows (virtual machine) not detecting clicks which happen too fast.

title: fixed the inScaling variable being set too early issue which was preventing…
message: fixed the inScaling variable being set too early issue which was preventing right-clicks in some situations.

title: Improved main screen layout.
message:
Improved main screen layout.

Fixed a bug in input mode in fit-to-screen scaling where the pointer was offset by a bit when the resolution of the remote screen was the same or smaller in one dimension but larger in the other.

title: revamped intro and help text.
message:
revamped intro and help text.

revamped right-drag mode for default input mode

working double-click (in windows) in both input modes with delay...

ported newest right-click changes from default input mode to touchpad mode.

title: a bit of delay added to ondoubletap to make double-click work in windows reliably.
message: a bit of delay added to ondoubletap to make double-click work in windows reliably.

title: fixed right-click flakiness in FF, and avoided the need to offset pointer and release.
message: fixed right-click flakiness in FF, and avoided the need to offset pointer and release.
